Design: {{ project_name }} ({{ in_feat }}->{{ out_feat }}, {{ n_ofm }} OFM PLIO).
This kernel owns only the output side; MM2S is a separate CU (pl/mm2s.cpp).

PING-PONG DOUBLE BUFFERING: each iteration is staged into one of two on-chip buffers;
while store_ddr() writes iteration N-1 to DDR from one buffer, recv_plio() fills the other
with iteration N from the PLIO shim, so PLIO receive overlaps DDR write-back. Only ONE
iteration is staged per buffer (not all n_iter), so n_iter is unbounded.

DDR layout (per iteration): contiguous 512-bit word i belongs to stream i % N, row i / N.
So for stream s at row r the DDR word is base + r*N + s. store_ddr writes DDR contiguously,
re-striping from buf[stream][row]. Each 512-bit word carries 4 x 128b AXI-stream beats.
{% if enable_pl_timing %}
PL timing on: s2mm emits one-beat axis event pulses (iter0 recv window + done) to the
shared tick_gen CU (sc=-wired), which owns the single free-running counter.
{% endif %}
